The paper discusses mechanisms supporting the mutual coordination of autonomous agents, which is a common topic in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses trust and credibility updating, which are important topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and social computing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper presents examples involving technology-mediated interaction, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
